# Defaults for `act`, so a local CI run matches the build server.
#
# act reads this file from the working directory. The build server runs the same
# workflows through Gitea Actions, whose runner is act -- so what you get here is
# the real thing rather than an approximation.

# Artifacts have nowhere to go unless act is given a directory to put them in.
# Without this, upload-artifact fails and you find out only at the end of a long
# LaTeX build. Contents land in .act-artifacts/<run>/<name>/.
--artifact-server-path .act-artifacts

# The default act image is minimal to the point of missing `sudo`, which the
# LaTeX install needs. This one is what act's own docs recommend for workflows
# written against GitHub's ubuntu-latest.
-P ubuntu-latest=catthehacker/ubuntu:act-latest
